Data: Wood to Finch, 1 run fullish and swinging a touch as Finch presses forward and steers one wide of mid-off to get going straight away

Wood to Finch, no run good length, up at 89mph as Finch comes across to defend softly
Wood to Finch, 1 wide pushes this one down the leg side
Wood to Finch, no run rising off a length, thudding into the bat label as Finch defends on off stump
Wood to Finch, no run pounds a length, tight lines and blocked once more

Willey to Marsh, no run good length, shaping in and out on off, Marsh blocks

Wood to Finch, no run length ball, defended around off stump

Wood to Finch, no run touch short, into the pads as Finch hangs back in the crease... high and leg side, though

Wood to Finch, no run touch wider, 88mph and left alone this time

Willey to Finch, 1 run fuller, shaping on the pads, worked wide of mid-on for one

Willey to Marsh, 1 run touch short outside off, Marsh taps it down in front of gully for a single

Willey to Finch, no run good length, 82mph outside off, left alone
Wood to Marsh, no run shortish and defended down into the leg side

Wood to Marsh, no run a touch leg side again, but Marsh can't get it away
Wood to Marsh, no run full on off, 88mph and stroked back down the pitch without timing, mid-off comes across
Wood to Marsh, no run pitched up, no width and again Marsh tucks the ball along the carpet to mid-off
Wood to Marsh, no run draws his length back a fraction, 88mph and spandex tight, all Marsh can do is defend into the covers - and that's a maiden over from Wood
Willey to Finch, no run good lines, shaping in as Finch comes across and blocks on off
Willey to Finch, no run on the spot again, good length and all Finch can do is defend once again

Wood to Marsh, no run back of a length, 88mph on the pads and tapped down square

Wood to Marsh, 1 run back of a length, 87mph and nudged off the body in front of square for one
Wood to Finch, 1 run full and clipped firmly wide of mid-on, Willey does well diving across to stop it one-handed and hurl in a shy at the stumps
Wood to Marsh, no run Marsh gets into line and defends
Willey to Finch, no run full and tempting on off stump, driven firmly but straight to mid-off
Willey to Finch, 1 run short and straight, Finch tickles the ball through backward square leg for one
Willey to Marsh, 1 run turned into the leg side
Willey to Finch, 1 run pitched up and punched to mid-off, tight single but the throw is wayward

Willey to Finch, no run full length, driven to mid-off
Ali to Marsh, no run round the wicket, tossed up on off stump, stroked to mid-off

Ali to Finch, OUT tossed up invitingly, Finch opens his body to go up and over... but only skews a thick outside edge to short third man! England have got rid of the dangerous Finch, Australia's most-experienced batsman, trying to get on top of Moeen but miscuing against the spin
Ali to Stoinis, no run pushed through on the stumps, Stoinis blocks
Ali to Stoinis, 1 run flat and quick, darted outside off and the ball comes off a thick outside edge, they scamper through as the throw comes in
Willey to Stoinis, 1 run hits a length in the channel, poked into a gap
Willey to Marsh, no run full, gets him coming forwards, driven uppishly but it bobbles between two men in the covers
Willey to Marsh, no run back of a length, chopped down into the off side
Willey to Marsh, 2 runs full, sliding in, 80mph and Marsh works a couple off his pads - Australia bring up their first 50 in the tenth over
Willey to Marsh, no run full length outside off, 83mph and picks out mid-off coming forwards
Willey to Marsh, no run drifting on to the pads but Marsh's leg glance runs quickly to Rashid at short fine leg and there's no run
Ali to Stoinis, 1 run tossed up from over the wicket and worked with the spin through square leg

Ali to Paine, FOUR runs slightly short and Paine is busy in the crease, rocks back and slams a cut through the covers... Willey gives chase and looks to have prevented four, but the umpires decide that he moved the boundary markers back as he slid through and the ball would have reached the rope, so a boundary is signalled
Ali to Paine, no run flat on off, better length and that's defended
Ali to Paine, no run tossed up and flicked slightly aerially to the leg side
Ali to Paine, no run Paine gets into line and defends
Rashid to Stoinis, no run pushes through a flat legbreak outside off, left alone by Stoinis
Rashid to Stoinis, no run pushed through on the stumps, blocked
Rashid to Stoinis, 1 run touch short, Stoinis stays back and punches a single to long-off
Rashid to Paine, 1 run tossed up on off, Paine taps one through the covers
Rashid to Stoinis, no run nicely slighted legbreak, gripping a touch as the batsman defends watchfully on off
Rashid to Stoinis, no run slider, out the front of the hand, Stoinis is equal to it and punches back towards the bowler
Ali to Paine, no run Paine uses the feet, comes down and clips the ball back to the bowler
Ali to Paine, 1 run now he drops in the crease and dabs a single wide of short third man
Ali to Stoinis, no run flighted, played with the spin to the on side
Ali to Stoinis, no run angled in with the arm, Stoinis punches back to the bowler
Ali to Stoinis, 1 run clips a single down the ground to long-on
Ali to Paine, 1 run floated up, Paine happy to knock it around and get the scoreboard ticking, one more through mid-on
Rashid to Paine, 1 run punched into the off side and Roy misfields at cover to give them a single
Rashid to Stoinis, no run flighted, on the stumps and knocked back down the track
Rashid to Stoinis, 1 run pushed through, googly or maybe another slider, worked off the pads
Rashid to Paine, no run now that is the wrong'un, Paine plays an expansive drive and is beaten, the ball sliding inches past off stump as Buttler then whips off the bails
Rashid to Paine, no run stays in the crease and works to the on side
Rashid to Paine, 1 run comes forward and punches one to long-off
Ali to Paine, no run pushed through on the stumps, dabbed into the covers
Ali to Paine, 1 run comes across and works a single down the ground
Ali to Stoinis, no run flat on the stumps, Stoinis prods it away
Ali to Stoinis, no run flighted, Stoinis tries to clip a drive down the ground but skews the ball towards mid-off
Ali to Stoinis, no run tossed up and punched to a fielder again... not looking the most convincing against spin, is Stoinis
Rashid to Paine, 1 run Rashid tosses the ball up and Paine drives for a single
Rashid to Stoinis, 1 run gives it some air, the legbreak on off stump, punched to long-off
Rashid to Paine, no run full, slow and floaty, Paine drives inside to out but picks out extra cover
Rashid to Paine, no run baited, tossed up wide of the stumps, Paine watches it spin away into the gloves
Rashid to Paine, 1 run comes forward and dabs a single wide of extra cover
Rashid to Stoinis, 2 runs flighted, outside the line of off, gets a stride in and belts a flat drive wide of long-off for a couple

Ali to Paine, OUT oh dear, what was that from Paine?! Makes a pre-meditated move outside off, brings out the reverse-sweep... and lobs a gentle top edge to short third man! He completely telegraphed his intentions, Buttler was almost far enough across to intercept the ball himself, but to compound that the execution was poor, hitting against the offspin, and he's gifted Moeen a third!
Ali to Maxwell, 2 runs full outside off, whipped into midwicket
Ali to Maxwell, no run gets across to off stump and worked with a closed face into the leg side
Ali to Maxwell, no run gets away with a leading edge this time as he again looks to flick to the leg side, falls short of cover
Ali to Maxwell, no run now he brings out a big sweep, doesn't make contact, gets taken on the pad, well outside the line
Ali to Maxwell, no run pushed into midwicket with a straight bat
Rashid to Stoinis, no run good length outside off, a leg-break, left alone
Rashid to Stoinis, 1 run full at off stump, pushed into the covers with an open face
Rashid to Maxwell, 1 run short of a length, onto the back foot, driven wide of short cover to long-off
Rashid to Stoinis, 1 run a fraction short outside off, plays back and drives to deep cover
Rashid to Maxwell, 1 run full and straight, pushed down the ground to long-on
Rashid to Stoinis, 1 run plays back again and punches to long-off
Ali to Stoinis, 2 runs gets well across onto off stump and sweeps behind square
Ali to Stoinis, no run back of a length outside off, pushed to the man at short mid-on
Ali to Stoinis, no run back and across, short of a length, pushed to cover
Ali to Stoinis, SIX runs that breaks the shackles! Uses his feet then lofts high over long-on. A clean swing of the bat
Ali to Stoinis, 1 run touch quicker and flatter, outside off, slides off a thickish outside edge into backward point
Ali to Maxwell, 2 runs works a straight ball off the pads through square and that's good running to make the second
Rashid to Stoinis, no run full outside off, bowled quite slowly, Stoinis pushes square to point
Rashid to Stoinis, 1 run full and straight, driven to long-off
Rashid to Maxwell, 1 run a straighter, quicker, delivery angled into the pads and pushed down to long-on
Rashid to Stoinis, OUT edged and gone! Caught behind...not the best ball Rashid has bowled, it's short outside off, Stoinis shapes to cut but can only managed a thin top edge to Buttler
Rashid to Agar, no run works a full ball back to the bowler
Rashid to Agar, no run very full, a yorker, dug out back down the pitch
Ali to Maxwell, no run good length at off stump, gets forward and works into midwicket
Ali to Maxwell, no run back to a slightly shorter ball, pushed to short mid-on
Ali to Maxwell, no run driven off the back foot to cover
Ali to Maxwell, no run forward outside off and defends a full delivery
Ali to Maxwell, no run short of a length, back into leg stump and drives to cover. Can't find the gap
Ali to Maxwell, no run works a straight ball into midwicket and that's a maiden for Moeen
Rashid to Agar, 1 run tucks a straight ball off his pads behind square
Rashid to Maxwell, 1 run leans back and cuts this from around off stump to deep cover
Rashid to Agar, 1 run full outside off, gets forward and drives wide of short cover
Rashid to Maxwell, no run a flat-batted drive finds cover as he tries to give himself a touch of room

Rashid to Agar, no run full and straight, driven to mid-off
Ali to Maxwell, no run full outside off, defended into midwicket
Ali to Maxwell, 1 run takes this off the stumps, leans back and drives to long-off

Ali to Maxwell, no run drives off the back foot to cover
Ali to Maxwell, 1 run sweeps a straight delivery to backward square leg, who is quite fine, so just a single...you can sense Maxwell getting twitchy
Root to Maxwell, 2 runs tucks a straight ball into square leg and scampers back for the second...that was reasonably tight
Root to Maxwell, 2 runs driven off the back foot through the off side, wide of the sweeper, to bring up Australia's hundred
Root to Maxwell, 1 run pushed to long-on
Root to Agar, no run round the wicket, angled in at middle and leg, full, pushed to midwicket

Ali to Agar, no run full and straight, driven to mid-off

Ali to Agar, no run full at off stump and driven to cover
Ali to Agar, 1 run full, outside off, gets forward and drives to deep cover...that's the halfway mark of the innings
Root to Agar, no run round the wicket, defended
Root to Agar, 1 run full and straight, driven down to long-off
Root to Maxwell, 1 run flicked off the pads behind square on the leg side...Maxwell now batting in a cap

Root to Agar, 1 run driven down the ground to long-off
Root to Maxwell, 1 run taken from around off stump through square leg
Ali to Maxwell, no run touch short outside off, doesn't get any timing, off the toe of the bat to cover

Ali to Maxwell, no run full outside off, driven to cover

Root to Maxwell, 1 run flicked into midwicket

Root to Maxwell, 1 wide fires this down the leg side, think he thought Maxwell was coming down the pitch
Root to Maxwell, no run starts to shuffle to leg then gets back in line and works to midwicket

Plunkett to Maxwell, no run good length, played off the front foot

Plunkett to Maxwell, no run full and straight, driven to mid-off...five dot balls to start

Wood to Agar, no run over the wicket, full at middle, flicked to mid-on
Wood to Agar, 1 run on the pads, tucked wide of midwicket

Plunkett to Maxwell, 1 run full and straight, driven firmly towards mid-on, Hales, on the edge of the circle...Hales throw is miles wide of the stumps but Maxwell was fine

Wood to Agar, no run touch fuller, at off stump, driven mid-off. Well bowled by Wood
Plunkett to Maxwell, 1 run short of a length, worked into midwicket and that's his fifty off 52 balls. Much needed for him and the team

Wood to Maxwell, no run big appeal for lbw but Rob Bailey says not out, a length ball that nipped back, was high and heading leg side
Wood to Maxwell, 1 run short of a length, pulled to deep square leg
Wood to Agar, no run full at off stump, driven into the pitch and it bounces to Morgan at cover for a crowd catch
Wood to Agar, no run back of a length at off stump, rolls his fingers across it, defended

Plunkett to Agar, 1 wide short outside leg stump, called wide
Plunkett to Agar, no run good length at off stump, pushed to mid-off

Plunkett to Agar, 1 run good length outside off, he leans forward and drives to deep point

Plunkett to Maxwell, 2 runs goes full and straight, clipped off his toes to long leg, takes on Rashid who doesn't produce the best of the throws. Would have been tight with a good return
Willey to Agar, 1 run over the wicket, 77mph around off stump, Agar nudges one down the ground
Willey to Maxwell, no run on the hips, Maxwell misses with a flick and it rolls towards short fine leg
Willey to Maxwell, 1 run length ball, 82mph and clipped for one to deep midwicket hanging back

Willey to Maxwell, 1 run chopped into the covers, Roy can only get a fingertip on it
Plunkett to Maxwell, 1 run short outside off and whipped away with a wristy pull to deep backward square leg

Plunkett to Maxwell, 2 runs 83mph and punched in front of deep cover, they come a back for a couple
Plunkett to Maxwell, no run cutting his fingers over the ball, mistimed back to the bowler

Plunkett to Maxwell, OUT flicked off his legs, but in the air... and Bairstow snags it on the run at deep square leg! Plunkett gets Maxwell, bit of luck involved as he pretty much struck that too well - an aggressive pick up but it went high, and sailed into the sweeper's path running back from midwicket! A tidy knock from Maxwell but he can't go on, England break the recovery stand
Plunkett to Agar, 1 run tucked away for a single
Rashid to Agar, no run over the wicket, flat legbreak outside off, Agar swipes it to mid-off
Rashid to Agar, no run tossed up and prodded back down the pitch
Rashid to Agar, 1 run flighted, Agar tucks a single down the ground to long-on

Rashid to Neser, no run gives this some air, the legbreak spinning away on middle, hits the splice as Neser defends

Willey to Agar, no run short of a length, forced off the back foot to mid-off

Willey to Agar, no run pitched up and deflected towards midwicket

Rashid to Neser, 1 run floated up on off stump, driven to wide long-off
Willey to Neser, no run full, clipped off the toes to midwicket

Rashid to Agar, OUT very full, Agar goes to sweep - misses and is plumb! Rob Bailey sends him on his way, no review from Agar, that struck him low down on the back pad as the ball straightened... only one place that delivery was ending up. Decent knock in adversity from Agar, but Australia are now seven down and in danger of not seeing out the overs
Rashid to Tye, no run legbreak on off, Tye covers the line as it straightens
Rashid to Tye, FOUR runs full and straight, the slider from Rashid... and Tye belts it unceremoniously back over the bowler's head for a no-nonsense four
Rashid to Tye, no run gets across and defends
Rashid to Tye, no run another shout for lbw, pitched on leg stump... but looks like that was a googly, would have been sliding down
Rashid to Tye, no run tossed up and defended into the covers
Plunkett to Neser, no run length ball, Neser pats it away

Plunkett to Neser, OUT goes for the slog down the ground, the ball not full enough for the shot... and mid-off settles under it for a simple catch! Neser tries to hit out and instead gets out, a second wicket for Plunkett and this innings is ending rather like it started
Plunkett to Tye, FOUR runs shot! High elbow, out of the meat, Tye showcases his straight drive again, slightly overpitched and he whacks it for another four
Plunkett to Tye, no run back of a length, 81mph and defended down into the covers from in front of the stumps
Plunkett to Tye, no run dug in short, Tye hangs back and flinches out of the way
Plunkett to Tye, no run short of a length, 79mph and possibly a cutter, short-armed towards mid-on
Rashid to Kane Richardson, no run tosses up the legbreak, Richardson defends his first ball

Rashid to Kane Richardson, no run flat on the stumps, Richardson drops back and defends with a straight bat
Rashid to Kane Richardson, 1 wide pushes the googly down the leg side
Rashid to Kane Richardson, no run flighted, this rips away as Richardson has a big old swing and a miss, Buttler breaks the bails but he had the back foot safely anchored
Plunkett to Tye, 1 run short outside off, Tye runs it away to third man
Plunkett to Kane Richardson, no run pitched up, 84mph and Richardson plinks one into the covers
Plunkett to Kane Richardson, no run prodded square from the crease
Plunkett to Kane Richardson, no run bangs in the short ball, Richardson isn't looking to play those
Plunkett to Kane Richardson, no run another bumper, this time he thinks about pulling, then thinks again

Wood to Tye, no run short ball, Tye rocks back and slugs it to midwicket

Wood to Stanlake, no run hits a length, 85mph and Stanlake prods to backward point
Wood to Stanlake, no run fizzes down another attempted yorker, up by the bootstraps but he's alert to the danger once more
Plunkett to Tye, no run tasty bouncer from Plunkett, crowding Tye as he tries to pull, is tucked up and beaten
Plunkett to Tye, no run back of a length, 84mph and past the outside edge as he tries to dab one from the crease

Plunkett to Tye, no run short of a length, cross seam and skidding on as Tye windmills across the line... and gets a top edge into his face! He seems okay, waggling his head back at the bowler, the grille did its job
Plunkett to Tye, SIX runs another short ball, goes for it again - SPANKED! Tye gets hold of an old-fashioned mow across the line and pounds six over deep midwicket! Back atcha
Plunkett to Tye, no run fuller, angling in and the ball deflects off a leading edge

Plunkett to Tye, OUT takes the pace off, Tye dabs at it off the back foot... but only succeeds in tickling a low edge through to Buttler! He took that well, diving forwards, Tye shakes his head but his fun is over - time to think about bowling, with just 214 to defend
Meanwhile, some mid-innings reading: The Redemption Tour, in association with Sky Sports

4.15pm: That, points out our stats man Gaurav Sundararaman, is Australia's second-lowest total batting first since the 2015 World Cup. Apart from an 84-run stand between Glenn Maxwell and Ashton Agar, Australia struggled through their innings, never got close to lighting the blue touchpaper, and were bowled out with 18 deliveries left in the can. They may be all about their values now, but there wasn't too much to

We'll wrap things up there for today. England are 1-0 up and the series now moves to Cardiff on Saturday. We'll see you then but for now from Gnasher, Alan and Miller it's goodbye and thanks for joining us.

England win by three wickets with plenty of time to spare. It's been one of their less convincing chases and for a little while it appeared they may stumble as they did against Scotland. But David Willey played calmly, an ODI career-best for him, and Australia were left to rue their own poor batting display. Eoin Morgan and Joe Root played nicely, but England's win was set up by the performance of their spinners e
England won by 3 wickets (with 36 balls remaining)
Player of the match is Moeen Ali, ENG
